20
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:09,470
Yes, Ma'am.

21
00:01:14,970 --> 00:01:17,380
<i>[Unexpected - Love Story in Maison Ginseiso]</i>

22
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:20,000
Shanghai, right?

23
00:01:20,050 --> 00:01:23,300
So, did you confess?

24
00:01:25,910 --> 00:01:28,970
I know you encouraged me to,

25
00:01:28,970 --> 00:01:32,160
but as always, my timing was bad.

26
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:36,010
Still, are you okay with that?

27
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:42,910
Our caretaker is trying to return to his roots.

28
00:01:44,970 --> 00:01:46,410
Besides...

29
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:50,650
if I bothered to confess,

30
00:01:50,650 --> 00:01:53,530
I'd only make myself lonelier.

31
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:11,330
<i>I assume Nishijima Itsuka wants nothing to do with me anymore.</i>

32
00:02:11,330 --> 00:02:13,810
<i>Do I have any other places to stay?</i>

33
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:14,940
Wait,

34
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,950
there's Tsuchiya.

35
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,150
No, never mind.

36
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:26,040
<i>Anyone but him!</i>

37
00:02:30,020 --> 00:02:31,350
<i>[Takeda Naoki: Are you free tonight?]</i>

38
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,850
<i>[Takeda Naoki]</i>

39
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:35,180
That's it!

40
00:02:36,210 --> 00:02:37,840
Takeda!

41
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,600
Shitara-san!

42
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,350
What's with the luggage?

43
00:02:41,350 --> 00:02:43,750
Look, I need to ask you a favor.

44
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:46,660
- Can I stay-
- Sir,

45
00:02:46,660 --> 00:02:49,100
I need to ask you a favor as well.

46
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,710
Are you Shitara-san?

47
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:56,280
Nice to meet you.

48
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:59,000
My name is Sennami.

49
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:10,070
This is delicious.

50
00:03:10,070 --> 00:03:12,960
It's both fragrant and refreshing, making it easy to drink.

51
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,730
Thank you very much.

52
00:03:14,730 --> 00:03:18,360
This "Sen no Sazanami" is our company's pride and joy.
<i>(T/N: Means "A Thousand Waves")</i>

53
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,440
After Sennami-san succeeded his father,

54
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:25,680
he became chief brewer and dedicated himself to research,

55
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:28,410
ultimately creating this "Sen no Sazanami."

56
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:31,590
It's truly a passion project, his life's work.

57
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:34,810
And yet, my passion project backfired.

58
00:03:34,810 --> 00:03:37,980
Without a method of mass production, our sales have dropped.

59
00:03:38,910 --> 00:03:43,210
Though I wish to restructure our procedures, I lack the necessary ideas.

60
00:03:44,050 --> 00:03:45,320
Shitara-san,

61
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,580
are there any solutions you can think of?

62
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:49,700
No matter how trivial it may be,

63
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:54,460
I will accept any and all advice that might improve my company.

64
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:57,910
Please help us out.

65
00:04:03,770 --> 00:04:05,680
<i>[A Premium Ginjo Sake, fresh from Toyama]
(T/N: a type of rice wine)</i>

66
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,670
<i>[Sen no Sazanami]</i>

67
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:12,600
<i>After giving it some thought, I've realized</i>

68
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:14,840
there's nothing I can do about it.

69
00:04:17,260 --> 00:04:19,020
- Welcome back!
- Oh, my gosh!

70
00:04:20,090 --> 00:04:21,550
You're actually still here.

71
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:24,490
- I'm so happy!
- Hey, you're breaking my tent!

72
00:04:24,490 --> 00:04:26,650
I heard everything from Nishijima.

73
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:28,720
Will you really be going to Shanghai?

74
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:34,810
That may be my only choice, realistically speaking.

75
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:37,860
Does that mean you're adamant about going?

76
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:42,810
Even if others ask for help,
<i>[Sen no Sazanami]</i>

77
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:44,510
I'm useless as I am now.

78
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:50,450
In that case, maybe I'm better off walking the given path.

79
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,930
<i>[Employment Contract]</i>

80
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:11,800
<i>[Shitara Kouichi]</i>

81
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:17,690
<i>What she said was accurate.</i>

82
00:05:17,690 --> 00:05:23,300
<i>Despite being in your prime, you are not working nor earning a living.</i>

83
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:28,430
<i>You, more than anyone else, must be most dissatisfied with yourself, right?</i>

84
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,700
I can't leave things as they are.

85
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:44,640
A farewell party?

86
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:47,050
We all want to celebrate your new life abroad.

87
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:48,550
No, I-

88
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:51,550
Farewell gatherings are a necessity for working people.

89
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:53,260
So let's go out with a bang!

90
00:05:53,260 --> 00:05:55,070
Well, I'm...

91
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:57,410
Here is your list.

92
00:05:59,250 --> 00:06:04,610
<i>Why am I running errands for my own party? Moreover...</i>

93
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:07,250
<i>It's filled with our requests for party food.</i>

94
00:06:07,250 --> 00:06:12,450
<i>Nishijima Itsuka, don't you have an ounce of remorse for rejecting me?</i>

95
00:06:22,050 --> 00:06:23,950
<i>No one's home?</i>

96
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,330
<i>What's going on?</i>

97
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,470
<i>[Safe travels, Mr. Caretaker! Thanks for your hard work.]</i>

98
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:32,440
<i>[Off to Shanghai!]</i>

99
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:35,730
<i>Did they seriously abandon the guest of honor?</i>

100
00:06:35,730 --> 00:06:37,150
<i>Unbelievable.</i>

101
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:43,560
Where did you all go-

102
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:46,590
Mother?

103
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,900
Why are you...

104
00:06:49,900 --> 00:06:56,070
The job in Shanghai that I offered you has been expedited.

105
00:06:56,070 --> 00:06:59,660
As such, I came to hear your response in person.

106
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,940
- In that case...
- May I come in?

107
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:16,090
<i>[Safe travels, Mr. Caretaker! Thanks for your hard work.]
[Off to Shanghai!]</i>

108
00:07:16,090 --> 00:07:17,870
I see you've made your choice.

109
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:21,650
Indeed, it is the correct one.

110
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:26,600
Do you always cook such a feast?

111
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,730
No.

112
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,990
We're holding a farewell party for me today.

113
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:37,910
Where is your room?

114
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:40,590
Due to some... circumstances,

115
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:44,410
I'm currently in a tent.

116
00:07:44,410 --> 00:07:46,250
A... tent?

117
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:48,820
O-Outside?

118
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:51,500
My actual room is inside.

119
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,280
I'll take you there later.

120
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:56,220
<i>Surprise!</i>

121
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:59,360
O-Oh, Shimako-san...

122
00:08:10,870 --> 00:08:12,380
Pardon the intrusion.

123
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:18,060
As I recall, you were at that dinner.

124
00:08:21,790 --> 00:08:25,830
We're set to begin our farewell party. Please join us if you'd like.

125
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:29,200
Thank you kindly.

126
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:33,390
Well...

127
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:39,800
there was a remark you made during our previous encounter

128
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,550
that has lingered on my mind.

129
00:08:42,550 --> 00:08:45,190
<i>When life tires you,</i>

130
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:50,060
<i>it is natural to take the easy way out.</i>

131
00:08:52,290 --> 00:08:57,360
Were those words directed at our boardinghouse?

132
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:05,480
Kouichi is destined to help many.

133
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:12,750
I raised him to become someone who will contribute to society.

134
00:09:12,750 --> 00:09:17,060
Yet... one setback was all it took

135
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:22,130
for him to give up on utilizing his strengths for the better.

136
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:27,980
Isn't that an extremely disrespectful action to take?

137
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:33,950
I... guess so.

138
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,910
Then, if you'll excuse me.

139
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:48,310
<i>[Caretaker Notes]</i>

140
00:10:03,410 --> 00:10:04,630
All right, then.

141
00:10:04,630 --> 00:10:08,700
Here's to Kou-chan's brand-new start.

142
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,760
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

143
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,010
Cheers.

144
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:22,260
Nao-san, that "thing."

145
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:23,950
Right, I almost forgot.

146
00:10:23,950 --> 00:10:27,810
We were out because we were buying this.

147
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:30,070
Here, it's your farewell gift.

148
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:34,830
A farewell gift? But I really...

149
00:10:34,830 --> 00:10:37,140
Just open it!

150
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:49,740
An apron?

151
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:53,480
We also considered getting you a necktie.

152
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:56,420
But Nishijima insisted and chose that apron.

153
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:57,480
What?

154
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,770
Right?

155
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:07,600
Mr. Caretaker, your cooking is mediocre,

156
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,380
and you fumble around with chores.

157
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:12,170
Still...

158
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:16,230
you work hard every day, without fail.

159
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,220
You've never chosen the easy way out.

160
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:31,570
So rather than a suit and tie, your apron style was...

161
00:11:33,130 --> 00:11:36,620
always the one I liked.

162
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:45,500
Thank you for all you've done for us.

163
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,280
Well then, I shall soon take my leave.

164
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,220
Please hand me your contract.

165
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:13,110
Mother...

166
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:16,140
I...

167
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:21,240
I cannot go to Shanghai.

168
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:28,330
I will not join your company either.

169
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:37,590
Then do you plan on continuing your job as a caretaker

170
00:12:37,590 --> 00:12:40,070
without earning a salary?

171
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:43,520
Sister Nao,

172
00:12:44,520 --> 00:12:46,300
could you hire me?

173
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,690
What?

174
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,310
Give this a look.

175
00:13:01,550 --> 00:13:06,160
"Proposal for improving Ginseiso's management"?

176
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:10,040
I gathered several pivotal points that bothered me about management here.

177
00:13:10,040 --> 00:13:13,310
If you agree with my proposals, sign this.

178
00:13:13,310 --> 00:13:15,150
An employment contract?

179
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:19,180
Exactly. It's so I can earn a salary as caretaker.

180
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,720
I'll be sure to draft a budget.

181
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:27,870
So please give me the chance to negotiate our terms.

182
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:31,180
Will you be able to make a living?

183
00:13:31,180 --> 00:13:34,240
If you're worried about income, I've thought it over.

184
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:37,640
My plan is to take on another job.

185
00:13:39,370 --> 00:13:41,100
In other words, having a "side hustle."

186
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:45,260
There are people out there who depend on my skills and experience.

187
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,790
While working as the caretaker,

188
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:52,650
I plan to be a consultant for various businesses, while helping them with management.

189
00:13:52,650 --> 00:13:53,600
Oh!

190
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:57,360
<i>Even if others ask for help, I'm useless as I am now.
[Sen no Sazanami]</i>

191
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:58,970
The sake company?

192
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:00,430
Exactly.

193
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:05,790
Mother...

194
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:11,850
now that I've set my mind to it, I'll become a professional caretaker!

195
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,570
To be honest,

196
00:14:21,330 --> 00:14:23,430
I first thought this job was absurd.

197
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:25,160
<i>Scrub every inch.</i>

198
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:28,500
<i>I questioned how I had fallen to such a low.</i>

199
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:31,990
<i>When will we eat a decent meal?</i>

200
00:14:31,990 --> 00:14:36,800
However, as I kept at my job...

201
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:39,140
<i>Not bad.</i>

202
00:14:39,140 --> 00:14:42,470
<i>They tasted all right, despite the misshapen look.</i>

203
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,810
<i>It's warm.</i>

204
00:14:45,810 --> 00:14:49,930
I got to see how satisfied people were with my work every day.

205
00:14:51,020 --> 00:14:56,720
As a man of ambition, this was the first time I'd felt a sense of accomplishment

206
00:14:56,720 --> 00:15:00,770
from something other than promotions, numbers, and such.

207
00:15:02,790 --> 00:15:04,800
That might be the reason...

208
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:11,880
I think... I've become a more decent human being.

209
00:15:14,610 --> 00:15:17,750
As I am now,

210
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:20,950
I can wholeheartedly accept myself when I'm weak

211
00:15:22,450 --> 00:15:24,330
and incompetent.

212
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:28,070
<i>I'm sorry for the trouble I caused you. I am really sorry.</i>

213
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:32,240
<i>I want to give you a proper apology.</i>

214
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:38,020
I'm sure my current self is a disappointment to you,

215
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:45,160
but I don't need the happiness of many.

216
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,980
I'm satisfied if even one person around me is happy.

217
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,620
That's...

218
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:58,350
who I am now.

219
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:28,580
Let's see, the ground beef is...

220
00:16:28,580 --> 00:16:30,900
nowhere to be seen.

221
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:35,130
It can't be helped. We'll have to mince this pork instead.

222
00:16:35,130 --> 00:16:37,670
And the skins...

223
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:41,320
will have to be made from scratch as well.

224
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:45,960
Dumplings...

225
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:53,390
You'll continue to be in these people's care, right?

226
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:56,620
Then they deserve at least another dish.

227
00:17:01,340 --> 00:17:06,090
That's too much filling. Keep balance in mind.

228
00:17:07,090 --> 00:17:08,450
<i>Looking good.</i>

229
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:10,960
<i>Like this?</i>

230
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,900
<i>Kou-chan, that looks wonderful!</i>

231
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:15,990
- Really?
- Yes, keep it up.

232
00:17:15,990 --> 00:17:18,560
All I had to do was watch you.

233
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,230
- Perhaps old habits kicked in.
- True.

234
00:17:20,230 --> 00:17:23,370
Yes, you're getting the hang of it!

235
00:17:26,060 --> 00:17:28,180
Well then... take care.

236
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:36,910
I took a glance at your notes.

237
00:17:36,910 --> 00:17:38,410
My notes?

238
00:17:39,890 --> 00:17:41,310
<i>[Caretaker Notes]</i>

239
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:44,310
<i>When I first began working,</i>

240
00:17:44,310 --> 00:17:46,460
I did the very same.

241
00:17:48,290 --> 00:17:50,200
Actually, those were a copy of yours.

242
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:05,150
Mother, you're the businessperson I respect most of all.

243
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:12,000
Now that your mind is set,

244
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,570
take the top spot, you hear?

